# Write 2-3 paragraph on Engineering

print('''Engineering is the application of scientific knowledge, mathematics, and practical experience to design, build, and improve structures, machines, systems, and processes that solve real-world problems. Engineers play a vital role in shaping modern society by developing technologies that enhance communication, transportation, healthcare, energy, and infrastructure. From bridges and buildings to software systems and smart devices, engineering connects theory with practical implementation to improve everyday life.

Different branches of engineering—such as civil, mechanical, electrical, computer, and electronics engineering—address specific challenges across various industries. With rapid advancements in technology, modern engineering now also includes emerging fields like artificial intelligence, renewable energy, robotics, and the Internet of Things (IoT). Engineers must continuously adapt, learn new tools, and apply innovative thinking to keep pace with changing global needs.

Beyond technical skills, engineering also emphasizes problem-solving, teamwork, ethics, and responsibility. Engineers are expected to design solutions that are not only efficient and cost-effective but also safe, sustainable, and socially beneficial. As the world faces challenges such as climate change, urbanization, and digital transformation, engineering remains a crucial profession in driving progress and building a better future.''')

